## 11. Key Architectural Decisions Summary

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| JS bundle blocking | Do NOT block in v1 | Compiled JSX is not human-readable prose; adds complexity; graceful degradation is hard |
| Client-side gate | Auth status API + Reader paywall check | Needed because Reader uses dynamic imports that bypass HTML-level blocking |
| Cookie per book | Yes, `pressy-auth-{bookSlug}` | Users may buy books independently; simple to manage per-book access |
| Stripe integration | Server-side in Worker | Stripe secret keys must be server-side; Workers can call Stripe API directly |
| KV vs D1 | KV | Simple key-value lookups; no relational queries needed |
| Manifest storage | `_pressy/manifest.json` in static output | Read via `ASSETS.fetch()` in middleware; no separate deployment needed |
| Middleware approach | Cloudflare Pages Functions `_middleware.ts` | No separate Worker deployment; collocated with static assets |

